s in the same sources, although the $^{14}$N/$^{15}$N ratios\nfrom N$_{2}$H$^{+}$ show a dispersion larger than that in HCN/HNC. Moreover, we\nhave found no correlation between D/H and $^{14}$N/$^{15}$N in HNC. These\nfindings indicate that: (1) the chemical evolution does not seem to play a role\nin the fractionation of nitrogen; (2) the fractionation of hydrogen and\nnitrogen in these objects are not related.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Sep 2017 10:24:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-07"}
